cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SOC

The paper deals with the problem of ranking vertices in a bipartite graph, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and social network analysis. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also presents a new solution that iteratively assigns scores to vertices and optimizes a regularization function, which involves machine learning techniques such as optimization and regularization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of ranking vertices in n-partite graphs, which involves graph theory and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experiments on real-world datasets, which involves practical applications of the proposed method, making cs.SI (Social and Information Systems) a possible sub-category.
